This paper deals with feature selection in high-dimensional classification or regression problems, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The paper proposes a new algorithm for feature selection, which is an extension of the Lasso algorithm. The paper also discusses the limitations of the Lasso algorithm in the context of biological problems, where features are often highly correlated. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
